This paper is about visual grounding, which is a problem in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new model for generating proposals, which involves multi-modal feature representation and ranking, indicating that it could also fit into the categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed model on benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
